WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:04.421
♪ Get up,
we're getting ready to roll ♪

00:04.421 --> 00:07.716
What about Kilimanjaro
for the honeymoon?

00:07.716 --> 00:09.218
You mean like to climb?

00:09.218 --> 00:10.552
It's more of
a strenuous hike.

00:11.637 --> 00:13.847
Is there a beach
at the top?

00:13.847 --> 00:17.809
Ooh, I don't want to lie,
but I do want you to say yes.

00:17.809 --> 00:18.977
Celina: Morning!

00:18.977 --> 00:20.687
Morning.
Morning.

00:20.687 --> 00:23.023
I made you coffee, and
I found your special milk.

00:23.023 --> 00:25.692
Thank you.
No.
No, no more special milk.

00:25.692 --> 00:27.277
No more extra pillows.

00:27.277 --> 00:29.696
Hotel Nolan
is officially closed.

00:29.696 --> 00:31.698
Two nights
is more than enough.

00:31.698 --> 00:34.409
I know. I'm back in my place
tonight, I swear.

00:34.409 --> 00:36.828
Uh, my new mattress
and white-noise machine
arrived today.

00:36.828 --> 00:38.705
I wish I had that machine
last night.

00:38.705 --> 00:40.916
That sound
was driving me crazy.

00:40.916 --> 00:42.960
I didn't notice anything.
I did.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.253
Every time I thought
it was going to stop,

00:44.253 --> 00:45.754
it just ramped
back up again.

00:45.754 --> 00:46.964
Was I snoring?

00:46.964 --> 00:49.132
No. It was much softer
than that.

00:49.132 --> 00:50.384
Like scratching.

00:50.384 --> 00:51.885
Oh, probably a raccoon.

00:51.885 --> 00:53.637
I'll check the crawl space
when I come home.

00:53.637 --> 00:55.639
What do you know about
the history of your house?

00:55.639 --> 00:57.849
I know what year
it was built.

00:57.849 --> 01:00.686
No, I mean, like,
has anyone died here?

01:00.686 --> 01:03.522
My house is not haunted.
You don't know that.

01:03.522 --> 01:06.567
The only unwanted entity
in this house,

01:06.567 --> 01:08.527
I'm looking at right now.

01:08.527 --> 01:11.989
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

01:11.989 --> 01:17.536
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

01:17.536 --> 01:20.289
Bah-bah-bah. Ohh.
[ Imitates explosion ]

01:20.289 --> 01:23.083
Any chance you're gonna
make it to the pediatrician
appointment today?

01:23.083 --> 01:25.294
I mean, if everyone just
confesses to their crimes,

01:25.294 --> 01:26.795
sure, but I doubt it.

01:26.795 --> 01:28.297
Well, the thing is

01:28.297 --> 01:30.340
Jack is due for
his vaccinations today.

01:30.340 --> 01:32.342
And you're usually there
to soothe him.

01:32.342 --> 01:34.553
He'll be fine. Just give him
Tylenol and cuddles.

01:34.553 --> 01:36.597
I know. I just don't want him
to feel betrayed.

01:36.597 --> 01:39.516
Like I took him to this place
he got jabbed by needles.

01:39.516 --> 01:41.310
Better he feels
<i>I</i> betrayed him?

01:41.310 --> 01:44.396
Y-Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

01:44.396 --> 01:46.523
I can see who's gonna be
the disciplinarian.

01:46.523 --> 01:48.358
I got to go.

01:48.358 --> 01:50.444
Bye, honey!

01:50.444 --> 01:54.698
[ <i>Children's music playing</i> ]

01:54.698 --> 01:56.116
[ Both laughing ]

01:56.116 --> 01:59.411
So, uh, I've been thinking.
Things are good between us.

01:59.411 --> 02:02.164
Yeah.
You know, we've been
through a lot,

02:02.164 --> 02:04.750
and we've come
through it stronger.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.960
I agree.
[ Chuckles ]

02:06.960 --> 02:11.048
So, uh, maybe it's time
to move in together.

02:12.049 --> 02:14.217
[ Chuckles ] Maybe. Sure.

02:14.217 --> 02:17.596
I mean, your place
is kind of small, though.

02:17.596 --> 02:20.599
I-I know, but with
my new promotion,

02:20.599 --> 02:24.186
I could maybe afford a cardboard
box deep in the Valley.

02:24.186 --> 02:27.481
Wait. You want
to buy a house?

02:27.481 --> 02:30.484
Yeah. That's what
grownups do, right?

02:30.484 --> 02:33.153
And I know you won't go anywhere
without Tamara.

02:33.153 --> 02:35.572
So what if we got a place
with a converted garage?

02:37.240 --> 02:39.409
I'll have to
think about it.

02:39.409 --> 02:40.786
Great.
Let's talk tonight.

02:40.786 --> 02:42.621
I'll start looking
at listings.

02:42.621 --> 02:45.457
So, I think I've proven myself,
you know,

02:45.457 --> 02:47.167
with my contributions to cases,

02:47.167 --> 02:49.711
and, you know,
I-I know I'm young,

02:49.711 --> 02:52.547
but I really think that I could
really help out around --

02:52.547 --> 02:54.633
Hey, sir, I was wondering
if I could have a minute.

02:54.633 --> 02:56.134
You got 20 seconds.
Go.

02:56.134 --> 02:57.552
Okay. So you remember
the diamond case, right?

02:57.552 --> 02:58.970
It was my --
my first case.

02:58.970 --> 03:00.847
Look, you're not gonna get
to the point at this rate.

03:02.599 --> 03:04.142
Okay.
I want to be a detective,

03:04.142 --> 03:05.560
and I will do anything
to make that happen.

03:05.560 --> 03:07.354
Is that it?

03:07.354 --> 03:09.356
Yes.
Alright.

03:09.356 --> 03:10.982
Shadow Harper
and Lopez today.

03:10.982 --> 03:12.984
-Hey, Tim.
-Yeah?

03:12.984 --> 03:14.820
I'm reassigning Aaron
for today.

03:14.820 --> 03:16.446
Lucy, that means
you're back on gopher duty.

03:18.115 --> 03:20.242
Okay.
[ Clears throat ]

03:20.242 --> 03:22.452
I could handle
one day alone.

03:22.452 --> 03:24.621
Is there some reason
you two can't ride together?

03:24.621 --> 03:27.624
♪♪

03:27.624 --> 03:30.001
Of course not.
No, sir.

03:30.001 --> 03:31.628
Good.

03:34.423 --> 03:35.382
Sorry.

03:37.551 --> 03:39.136
Um...

03:39.136 --> 03:40.887
I'll go get the gear.
Okay.

03:40.887 --> 03:43.223
Officer Thorsen
reporting for duty.

03:43.223 --> 03:44.558
Grey just
signed off on it.

03:44.558 --> 03:46.101
Told you he would.

03:46.101 --> 03:47.686
I didn't realize
you wanted to be a detective.

03:47.686 --> 03:49.896
I mean, to me, it seems like
the most effective way

03:49.896 --> 03:52.441
to make sure other people
aren't railroaded like I was.

03:52.441 --> 03:55.235
'Cause the detective
that was assigned <i>my</i> case,

03:55.235 --> 03:57.446
he dropped the ball
every step of the way.

03:57.446 --> 03:59.281
Well, he <i>was</i> French.

03:59.281 --> 04:01.825
So, what, you've never seen,
like, a bad American detective?

04:01.825 --> 04:03.493
That's fair.

04:03.493 --> 04:05.162
But I do have to
warn you,

04:05.162 --> 04:08.039
being a detective is nothing
like being on patrol.

04:08.039 --> 04:10.417
The hours are brutal,

04:10.417 --> 04:12.961
and the cases are
emotionally devastating

04:12.961 --> 04:15.088
in a way that patrol
can't prepare you for.

04:15.088 --> 04:17.215
Are you sure
you want this?

04:17.215 --> 04:18.592
Yes, I'm sure.

04:18.592 --> 04:21.261
What do you say
we start with a test?
Oh.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.096
How about a game
of five questions?

04:23.096 --> 04:24.848
Okay. Let's go. Yeah.

04:24.848 --> 04:27.350
As a detective, you need to
ask the right questions,

04:27.350 --> 04:29.519
so I'll send you the first page
of a case file.

04:29.519 --> 04:32.773
You can ask us five questions
and five questions only.

04:32.773 --> 04:34.858
So think carefully about what
you need to know to solve it.

04:34.858 --> 04:36.860
Oh, I got this.

04:36.860 --> 04:38.653
Alright,
so the records get dodgy,

04:38.653 --> 04:41.156
but so far I haven't found
anyone who's died in your house.

04:41.156 --> 04:42.991
On your land
is a bigger question.

04:42.991 --> 04:45.076
Okay. I appreciate
all the hard work.

04:45.076 --> 04:47.120
I think I'm just gonna
call an exterminator.

04:47.120 --> 04:49.372
Look, I-I think you need
to broaden your understanding

04:49.372 --> 04:52.209
of what's possible.
Have you tried ayahuasca?

04:52.209 --> 04:53.794
Nolan: <i>Hmm.</i>

04:53.794 --> 04:55.754
<i>You know, it really shifts</i>
<i>the way you see the world.</i>

04:55.754 --> 04:57.172
<i>I think</i>
<i>it'd be good for you.</i>

04:57.172 --> 04:59.299
<i>Is that the one that makes you</i>
<i>vomit uncontrollably?</i>

04:59.299 --> 05:00.425
<i>It's very cleansing.</i>

05:00.425 --> 05:02.344
<i>Yeah, I-I think</i>
<i>I want to keep</i>

05:02.344 --> 05:04.346
<i>my perception</i>
<i>the way it is.</i>

05:04.346 --> 05:07.224
[ Police radio chatter ]

05:12.187 --> 05:14.022
So...

05:14.022 --> 05:16.024
how's single life going?

05:16.024 --> 05:17.984
It's good.
No one to complain

05:17.984 --> 05:20.070
when I watch football
all Sunday.

05:21.238 --> 05:22.906
You didn't leave
the house once?

05:22.906 --> 05:24.407
I walked Kojo.

05:24.407 --> 05:25.867
Tim, what?
[ Chuckles ]

05:25.867 --> 05:27.577
I spend all week
outside.

05:27.577 --> 05:30.121
No, I know, but we live
in a vibrant city.

05:30.121 --> 05:32.457
There's always <i>something</i>
amazing going on.

05:32.457 --> 05:34.251
Okay, so, don't get me wrong,
I love L. A.,

05:34.251 --> 05:36.211
but it is <i>not</i>
a vibrant city, okay?

05:36.211 --> 05:38.964
It's a loosely stitched together
patchwork of strip malls.

05:40.549 --> 05:42.300
You're hopeless.

05:42.300 --> 05:44.010
[ Cellphone rings ]

05:45.846 --> 05:47.597
Chris:
<i>Hey! You busy?</i>

05:47.597 --> 05:50.934
Uh, no.
Wh-Where are you?

05:50.934 --> 05:53.520
An open house.
It was on my way to work.

05:53.520 --> 05:54.855
Uh, what do you think?

05:54.855 --> 05:56.189
It needs some work,

05:56.189 --> 05:57.607
<i>but, uh,</i>
<i>it's three bedrooms.</i>

05:57.607 --> 06:00.986
Yeah, I -- I can't really see
anything. Can we talk later?

06:00.986 --> 06:02.487
Okay. Love you.

06:02.487 --> 06:04.364
Yeah.

06:04.364 --> 06:06.783
Are you -- Are you and Chris,
uh, moving in together?

06:06.783 --> 06:08.660
No. Uh, it's --
I mean, he seems to
think you are.

06:08.660 --> 06:10.954
Yeah, I mean,
I don't know.

06:10.954 --> 06:13.206
He kind of sprang it on me
this morning.

06:16.209 --> 06:17.586
You guys are happy,
right?

06:17.586 --> 06:19.546
Yeah.
Those are the obvious
next steps.

06:19.546 --> 06:21.715
Yeah, no, we're super happy.
It's -- It's good.

06:21.715 --> 06:24.634
Dispatch: <i>7-Adam-100,</i>
<i>I have an in-progress vandalism</i>

06:24.634 --> 06:26.636
<i>on West 3rd</i>
<i>south of Olympic.</i>

06:26.636 --> 06:28.847
Yeah. Show us responding.

06:28.847 --> 06:31.266
[ Siren wails ]

06:31.266 --> 06:33.018
Krishna: No, no, no, no!
Not the Corvette!

06:33.018 --> 06:34.311
You should've
thought of that

06:34.311 --> 06:35.312
before you flirted
with that whore!

06:35.312 --> 06:37.063
Babe! Aah!
Lucy: Oh, my God.

06:37.063 --> 06:38.523
Our accountant?
She's 60!

06:38.523 --> 06:40.901
And a stone-cold fox!

06:40.901 --> 06:44.279
Tim: <i>Okay, ma'am -- ma'am,</i>
<i>put down the golf club.</i>
Krishna: <i>Oh, yeah?</i>

06:44.279 --> 06:45.488
Sir, no!
Put the golf club down!

06:45.488 --> 06:47.574
You wouldn't dare!
Is this what you want?

06:47.574 --> 06:49.743
<i>Okay, that's it!</i>
<i>Enough! Weapons down!</i>

06:49.743 --> 06:52.412
<i>Weapon?</i>
<i>It's a golf club.</i>

06:52.412 --> 06:53.747
<i>Now.</i>

06:53.747 --> 06:56.499
<i>I -- Look, Officer,</i>
<i>this is a misunderstanding.</i>

06:56.499 --> 06:58.877
<i>Who called you?</i>
That doesn't matter.

06:58.877 --> 07:01.796
<i>It was the busybody</i>
<i>across the street, wasn't it?</i>

07:01.796 --> 07:04.299
I bet she's posting
on Nextdoor!

07:04.299 --> 07:05.675
<i>Yeah, yeah, yeah,</i>
<i>of course she is.</i>

07:05.675 --> 07:07.594
<i>You know, what else has she got</i>
<i>in her sad little life?</i>

07:07.594 --> 07:11.139
She needs to put down the phone
and take in her garbage bins!

07:11.139 --> 07:12.724
<i>Yeah.</i>
<i>Yeah, yeah, yeah.</i>

07:12.724 --> 07:14.392
<i>Actually, can you guys</i>
<i>do something about that, huh?</i>

07:14.392 --> 07:15.935
<i>She just leaves them</i>
<i>out there for days.</i>

07:15.935 --> 07:18.063
<i>Not our jurisdiction.</i>

07:18.063 --> 07:19.356
[ Sweetly ]
Okay. Fine.

07:21.733 --> 07:24.235
Mm. So where do you want
to go for brunch?
In bed.

07:24.235 --> 07:26.279
<i>Mmm. I like the way</i>
<i>you're thinking.</i>

07:26.279 --> 07:28.615
Okay. Either of you want
to make a report

07:28.615 --> 07:30.200
about the damage
to your cars?

07:30.200 --> 07:31.910
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>
<i>At this point,</i>

07:31.910 --> 07:33.703
<i>we have the body shop</i>
<i>on speed dial.</i>

07:33.703 --> 07:40.001
♪♪

07:40.001 --> 07:44.547
So, have you thought of
your first question?

07:44.547 --> 07:46.091
Yes.

07:46.091 --> 07:48.968
I already went over the file
you gave me.

07:48.968 --> 07:50.679
The remains were found
on the grounds

07:50.679 --> 07:52.347
of the La Brea Tar Pits
complex,

07:52.347 --> 07:55.350
and a female guard went missing
one month prior.

07:55.350 --> 07:56.601
Correct.

07:56.601 --> 07:58.687
And it's always
the boyfriend.

07:58.687 --> 08:01.439
Okay. First question.
Was she seeing anyone?

08:01.439 --> 08:03.858
Yes. And he also worked
at the museum.

08:03.858 --> 08:05.443
A paleontologist.

08:05.443 --> 08:07.487
Oh, okay. So he had access
to the grounds.

08:07.487 --> 08:10.156
Interesting.
Did he have an alibi?

08:10.156 --> 08:11.950
No, he did not.

08:11.950 --> 08:13.493
Okay.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.912
So why haven't you and Bailey
set a date?

08:15.912 --> 08:18.289
Oh, we're enjoying
being engaged.

08:18.289 --> 08:20.917
Hm. Have something to do
with her crazy ex?

08:20.917 --> 08:23.420
Are they even divorced?

08:23.420 --> 08:25.046
Uh, yeah, they have been
for a while now.

08:25.046 --> 08:26.589
How did you
even know about that?

08:26.589 --> 08:28.174
I mean, cops gossip.

08:28.174 --> 08:30.885
Really? About me?
What else do they say?

08:30.885 --> 08:32.554
Well, they don't say, like,
anything bad.

08:32.554 --> 08:34.013
They just mention--

08:34.013 --> 08:35.598
[ Engine revs, tires screech ]
Whoa.

08:35.598 --> 08:36.766
Light it up.

08:36.766 --> 08:37.809
[ Siren wails ]

08:40.770 --> 08:42.272
[ Tires screech ]

08:46.484 --> 08:47.986
Ma'am?

08:49.988 --> 08:52.532
Uh, ma'am, can you turn
the engine off for me?

08:52.532 --> 08:54.492
Pam: I can't stop. I have to
keep driving. I'm sorry.

08:54.492 --> 08:56.870
Ma'am, I need you
to stop the car.

08:56.870 --> 08:57.996
<i>What is that</i>
<i>around your neck?</i>

08:57.996 --> 08:59.581
<i>He made me put it on.</i>

08:59.581 --> 09:02.959
<i>He said to drive</i>
<i>or he'd kill me.</i>

09:02.959 --> 09:04.252
<i>Ma'am, is that a bomb?</i>

09:04.252 --> 09:06.046
<i>[ Crying ]</i>
<i>I have to go.</i>

09:06.046 --> 09:07.672
<i>I'm sorry.</i>
<i>I don't want to die.</i>

09:07.672 --> 09:09.132
<i>I have to go.</i>

09:09.132 --> 09:10.550
<i>Ma'am? Ma'am?</i>
<i>No. No!</i>

09:10.550 --> 09:12.010
[ <i>Tires squeal</i> ]

09:12.010 --> 09:15.096
♪♪

09:19.100 --> 09:23.772
Pilot: <i>Air-3 is lifting off now.</i>
<i>ETA -- 5 minutes from target.</i>

09:23.772 --> 09:26.483
You made the right call. We have
to assume it's a real explosive.

09:26.483 --> 09:28.193
Coordinating with
the bomb squad now.

09:28.193 --> 09:29.944
Yes, sir.
What would you like us to do?

09:29.944 --> 09:32.697
Follow her, but stay
out of radio range.
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

09:32.697 --> 09:34.365
If the bomb has
a remote trigger,

09:34.365 --> 09:37.619
our radio signal
could set it off.

09:37.619 --> 09:38.828
Celina: Dropping back.
<i>We'll clear the streets.</i>

09:38.828 --> 09:40.705
Air support's on its way.

09:40.705 --> 09:41.998
Sir, maybe we can get
a court order

09:41.998 --> 09:43.249
for all the cell carriers.

09:43.249 --> 09:44.793
Get phone numbers attached
to her home address.

09:44.793 --> 09:46.294
It's already in process.

09:46.294 --> 09:48.338
7-Adam-100, 2331,

09:48.338 --> 09:50.215
stand by
for victim information.

09:50.215 --> 09:52.092
Copy.
Copy.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.260
Where do you want us?
<i>Scout for a staging area.</i>

09:54.260 --> 09:56.387
Bomb squad needs
a wide-open space.

09:56.387 --> 09:58.264
We have to limit
potential casualties.

09:58.264 --> 10:00.141
There's an empty lot
near Nolan's location.

10:00.141 --> 10:02.310
Perfect.
I'll send backup to you now.

10:02.310 --> 10:05.146
So, Harper, Lopez, Nolan says
the driver's under duress.

10:05.146 --> 10:06.856
Said she was told
to keep driving

10:06.856 --> 10:08.108
or the bomb would detonate.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.859
Did he give her
a destination?

10:09.859 --> 10:11.861
No. Doesn't seem to be
about a target.

10:11.861 --> 10:13.530
<i>She's</i> the target.

10:13.530 --> 10:15.573
<i>So we need to find</i>
<i>whatever we can on her.</i>

10:15.573 --> 10:17.242
Whoever chose her
did it for a reason.

10:17.242 --> 10:19.369
We're on it.
Nolan...

10:19.369 --> 10:21.746
bomb squad needs to know
what they're dealing with.
Can you get a picture?

10:21.746 --> 10:23.456
No problem.
Turning off radio, going dark.

10:25.291 --> 10:26.543
Want you to pull up
next to that car.

10:26.543 --> 10:27.752
Try and stay parallel.

10:27.752 --> 10:29.295
The bomb car?
Yeah.

10:29.295 --> 10:30.964
Okay. Getting closer
to the bomb car.

10:30.964 --> 10:34.384
[ Engine revs ]

10:34.384 --> 10:35.510
Alright.

10:35.510 --> 10:36.511
Closer. Alright.

10:36.511 --> 10:37.929
[ Crying ]

10:37.929 --> 10:41.015
Uh, it's a hinged collar
secured around her neck,

10:41.015 --> 10:43.518
kind of like handcuffs.
Nolan...

10:43.518 --> 10:46.312
With quarter-twenty tapped
standoffs at regular intervals.

10:46.312 --> 10:47.522
Nolan.

10:47.522 --> 10:50.733
The explosive is built
into the side of the unit.

10:50.733 --> 10:53.111
Contains C-4. It's connected
with red and green wires.

10:53.111 --> 10:54.737
J-John!
Almost done.

10:54.737 --> 10:55.738
No, we have to fall back.

10:55.738 --> 10:57.115
I just need a better look
at the clasp.

10:57.115 --> 10:58.741
It's -- It's secured
under her chin

10:58.741 --> 11:01.953
with a pin post lock, dual-post
shackle-style mechanism.

11:01.953 --> 11:04.998
[ Tires screech ]

11:04.998 --> 11:07.167
God. Did you get it?
That was some slick driving.

11:07.167 --> 11:08.751
Thanks.

11:08.751 --> 11:11.004
Okay. Hopefully,
that's all they need.

11:11.004 --> 11:12.755
I-I mean, that was
a pretty precise description.

11:12.755 --> 11:15.383
Oh, in my previous life,
I was a contractor.

11:15.383 --> 11:17.093
I'm surprised you remember
your past lives.

11:17.093 --> 11:18.303
Celina.

11:18.303 --> 11:20.346
I'm sorry.
Just kidding.

11:20.346 --> 11:21.639
Lopez: We're on our way
to the victim's house now.

11:21.639 --> 11:23.933
I need a scrub of
all social-media posts.

11:23.933 --> 11:25.643
Thanks.
Pam's a lawyer.

11:25.643 --> 11:27.562
We should start
with her client list.

11:27.562 --> 11:29.272
I already put in a call
to her old law firm.

11:29.272 --> 11:31.149
She had
a criminal-defense practice,

11:31.149 --> 11:32.775
so there's no telling
who she pissed off.

11:32.775 --> 11:34.527
Look at you.

11:34.527 --> 11:36.487
I mean, if I want to become
detective before I'm 30,

11:36.487 --> 11:38.072
I got to be on my game,
right?

11:38.072 --> 11:40.408
Does that mean you've thought
of your third question?

11:40.408 --> 11:42.493
I have, but I don't
want to just assume

11:42.493 --> 11:44.162
that the paleontologist
boyfriend did it,

11:44.162 --> 11:47.290
so I need a more complete
picture of the guard's life.

11:47.290 --> 11:48.958
Does she have
a criminal record?

11:48.958 --> 11:51.461
As a matter of fact,
she was under investigation

11:51.461 --> 11:52.921
at the time
of her disappearance.

11:52.921 --> 11:56.216
They suspected her of stealing
small artifacts from the museum

11:56.216 --> 11:57.967
and selling them
on the black market.

11:57.967 --> 11:59.427
Maybe she got greedy

11:59.427 --> 12:01.262
or threatened
to go to the police,

12:01.262 --> 12:03.973
and whoever she was working with
decided she was a liability.

12:05.183 --> 12:07.810
Is there a question
in there?

12:07.810 --> 12:09.020
Not yet.

12:09.020 --> 12:10.355
[ Police radio chatter ]

12:10.355 --> 12:12.523
Perfect.
There's plenty of space to --

12:12.523 --> 12:15.235
[ Punk music playing,
skaters chattering ]

12:15.235 --> 12:16.486
Boy: Awesome, dude.

12:16.486 --> 12:18.279
Flag on the play.
Parking lot is not empty.

12:18.279 --> 12:19.906
Sgt. Grey:
<i>Clear it out now.</i>

12:19.906 --> 12:22.242
I'm redirecting the bomb squad
to your location.

12:22.242 --> 12:26.412
<i>Hey! LAPD! We need you guys</i>
<i>to clear out! Let's go!</i>

12:26.412 --> 12:28.790
There's a bomb!
Run like hell!

12:28.790 --> 12:30.166
Let's go!

12:30.166 --> 12:31.751
[ Children shouting ]

12:31.751 --> 12:33.920
Boy: Let's roll!
[ Skaters shouting
indistinctly ]

12:33.920 --> 12:35.755
[ Siren wails ]

12:37.715 --> 12:39.842
We have Pam's
mobile number.

12:39.842 --> 12:42.303
[ Cellphone rings ]

12:42.303 --> 12:44.889
Hi. It's Pam, right?
My name is John.

12:44.889 --> 12:47.225
We have the bomb squad
on the way to help you out.

12:47.225 --> 12:48.643
You are gonna be okay.

12:48.643 --> 12:50.436
Right now,
I need you to follow us.

12:50.436 --> 12:51.938
Can you do that?

12:51.938 --> 12:53.273
I need to call my mom.

12:53.273 --> 12:54.899
I need to tell her
that I love her.

12:54.899 --> 12:58.278
We can do that, but right now,
I need you to follow us

12:58.278 --> 13:00.071
so we can meet up
with the bomb squad, okay?

13:00.071 --> 13:01.155
He told me
to keep driving.

13:01.155 --> 13:02.907
He said that I would die
if I didn't.

13:02.907 --> 13:04.742
Pam, that's a lie.

13:04.742 --> 13:07.537
Bomb squad says there's no GPS
on your collar, alright?

13:07.537 --> 13:09.205
He can't tell
if you're stopped or not.

13:09.205 --> 13:09.998
Are you sure?

13:09.998 --> 13:11.958
Yes.
Yes, Pam, I am sure.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.167
Now we're gonna pull out
in front of you

13:13.167 --> 13:14.711
and you're gonna
follow us, okay?

13:14.711 --> 13:15.670
[ Breathes shakily ]
Okay.

13:15.670 --> 13:17.964
[ Engine revs ]

13:17.964 --> 13:19.757
[ Siren wails ]

13:19.757 --> 13:21.592
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

13:21.592 --> 13:25.138
Pilot: <i>I have a visual.</i>
<i>Will maintain contact.</i>

13:25.138 --> 13:26.764
Alright, Pam.

13:26.764 --> 13:27.807
Now, I want you to park

13:27.807 --> 13:29.600
right up next
to the orange cone

13:29.600 --> 13:31.102
that Sergeant Bradford
is setting out.

13:31.102 --> 13:33.521
Okay?
Okay.

13:33.521 --> 13:37.233
♪♪

13:37.233 --> 13:41.404
Yeah, you got it.
Gonna take you to a safe spot.

13:41.404 --> 13:43.948
Alright, Pam, just checking in.
How are you doing?

13:43.948 --> 13:47.201
Um...not great.

13:47.201 --> 13:49.120
Please get this thing
off of me.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.955
That's what
we're here to do.

13:53.041 --> 13:56.252
Alright. And there they are.
Bomb squad is here.

13:56.252 --> 13:58.588
We're gonna have you
out of that in no time.

13:58.588 --> 14:01.841
Now, Pam, earlier you said you
wanted me to call your mother.

14:01.841 --> 14:03.718
Is there anyone else
you want me to get ahold of?

14:03.718 --> 14:06.846
No. Not really.

14:06.846 --> 14:08.181
Is that pathetic?

14:08.181 --> 14:10.975
Not at all.

14:10.975 --> 14:12.518
There's nothing like
a traumatic event

14:12.518 --> 14:16.272
to make you realize that your --
that your life is empty.

14:16.272 --> 14:18.858
Come on, Pam.
I don't believe that.

14:18.858 --> 14:19.776
[ Sniffles ]

14:19.776 --> 14:22.779
My entire life is work.

14:22.779 --> 14:25.656
I have no friends.

14:25.656 --> 14:27.575
I'm completely alone.

14:27.575 --> 14:30.620
You're not alone, Pam.
'Cause I'm here now.

14:30.620 --> 14:33.915
Everyone here
is here to help you.

14:33.915 --> 14:36.250
I need you to cut off
your engine now, Pam.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.419
You see that guy behind you
in the doughboy suit?

14:38.419 --> 14:41.422
That's Mike. Mike is absolutely
the best there is.

14:41.422 --> 14:44.759
Alright? He's gonna get you
out of there in no time.

14:44.759 --> 14:47.095
The only problem is, uh,

14:47.095 --> 14:49.305
he tells very bad
dad jokes,

14:49.305 --> 14:51.349
so I'm gonna have to
apologize in advance.

14:51.349 --> 14:53.643
Alright.
He's there at your window.

14:53.643 --> 14:55.770
Mike: <i>It's locked.</i>

14:55.770 --> 14:58.231
I just need you to reach down
and open the door, okay, Pam?

14:58.231 --> 15:01.109
I can't.
I can't move.
Hey...

15:01.109 --> 15:03.402
Yes, you can do this.
You can do this, Pam.

15:03.402 --> 15:05.530
Just take a --
take a nice deep breath.

15:05.530 --> 15:07.740
Reach down.
Unlock that door.

15:10.118 --> 15:13.996
[ Crying ] I-I can't.
I can't. I can't.

15:13.996 --> 15:17.500
You got this.
I know as soon as I move,
this thing's gonna go off!

15:17.500 --> 15:20.044
No, come on. Come on, Pam.
It's almost over.

15:20.044 --> 15:21.420
Mike is right there.

15:21.420 --> 15:23.381
You just
need to open the door for him.

15:23.381 --> 15:26.134
Okay, okay.
Okay, okay, okay.
You got this, Pam.

15:26.134 --> 15:28.177
Okay.
Okay.

15:28.177 --> 15:29.679
[ Exhales sharply ]
I'm gonna reach over.

15:29.679 --> 15:31.430
I'm gonna --

15:31.430 --> 15:33.432
I'm gonna unlock it,
okay?

15:33.432 --> 15:36.394
[ Collar beeping ]
It started beeping.

15:36.394 --> 15:37.770
Do you hear that?
Why is it beeping?

15:37.770 --> 15:39.730
It's beeping.
Why is it beeping?

15:39.730 --> 15:41.983
Uh, don't worry about that, Pam.
Just open the door, okay?

15:41.983 --> 15:42.859
[ Collar beeping rapidly ]
Just open that door.

15:44.360 --> 15:46.154
[ Officers screaming ]

15:46.154 --> 15:51.284
♪♪

15:55.538 --> 15:57.707
[ Sirens wailing,
skateboarders chattering ]

15:57.707 --> 15:58.499
Nolan: Go get those kids
out of here!

15:58.499 --> 15:59.500
Celina: Okay.

15:59.500 --> 16:01.377
-This is crazy.
-It's crazy.

16:01.377 --> 16:02.253
Girl: Yo, this is
so crazy, yo. Wait.

16:02.253 --> 16:04.172
We were just skating.
Look, look.

16:04.172 --> 16:05.339
Look at this.
Look at this.

16:05.339 --> 16:07.425
I need you all to back up
another 10 yards.

16:07.425 --> 16:10.136
<i>Yo, Officer, what happened?</i>
<i>I heard a lady blew up?</i>

16:10.136 --> 16:11.804
We're not sharing
any information at this time.

16:11.804 --> 16:12.805
Back up!

16:12.805 --> 16:14.015
[ Siren wails ]

16:14.015 --> 16:16.100
[ Fire extinguisher spraying ]

16:18.352 --> 16:21.314
[ <i>Indistinct conversations</i> ]

16:21.314 --> 16:22.481
<i>I pushed back</i>
<i>the perimeter.</i>

16:22.481 --> 16:23.482
<i>Good.</i>

16:23.482 --> 16:25.651
<i>Do you think</i>
<i>she felt it?</i>

16:25.651 --> 16:26.527
<i>Her death?</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

16:26.527 --> 16:28.279
<i>No.</i>

16:28.279 --> 16:30.740
But everything up to that point
was torture.

16:30.740 --> 16:32.283
What'd the bomb squad
say?

16:32.283 --> 16:33.492
They confirmed what
we already suspected.

16:33.492 --> 16:35.077
<i>Device appears</i>
<i>to be homemade</i>

16:35.077 --> 16:36.829
<i>using items you can find</i>
<i>at any hardware store.</i>

16:36.829 --> 16:38.623
<i>Do they know what</i>
<i>triggered the explosion?</i>

16:38.623 --> 16:40.458
<i>Most likely, the device</i>
<i>was on a timer,</i>

16:40.458 --> 16:42.001
<i>but they need to put the bomb</i>
<i>back together to be sure.</i>

16:42.001 --> 16:44.128
<i>Ah, that's gonna be</i>
<i>a hell of a jigsaw puzzle.</i>

16:44.128 --> 16:46.422
<i>I'm sure videos are already</i>
<i>popping up on social media.</i>

16:46.422 --> 16:48.007
<i>And the news choppers</i>
<i>are already here.</i>

16:48.007 --> 16:49.800
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

16:49.800 --> 16:52.386
Okay, well, if her car and her
license plate get leaked online,

16:52.386 --> 16:53.930
<i>it's not gonna be long</i>
<i>till her name does, too.</i>

16:53.930 --> 16:56.515
<i>Ohh, I can't imagine</i>
<i>finding out something</i>

16:56.515 --> 16:58.935
<i>about someone I love</i>
<i>like this on ClipTalk.</i>

16:58.935 --> 17:00.811
<i>We're not gonna</i>
<i>let that happen.</i>

17:00.811 --> 17:02.438
<i>Nolan, I want you and Juarez</i>
<i>to go to the victim's house.</i>

17:02.438 --> 17:03.189
<i>Right.</i>

17:05.650 --> 17:07.193
<i>Who would do</i>
<i>something like this?</i>

17:09.320 --> 17:11.447
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

17:11.447 --> 17:13.282
It's officially
a homicide.

17:15.701 --> 17:17.536
Was anyone else
injured?

17:17.536 --> 17:19.747
Nothing serious.

17:19.747 --> 17:22.375
That's strange, right?

17:22.375 --> 17:24.835
I mean, bombs are usually
for mass-casualty events.

17:24.835 --> 17:27.755
If you want to kill one person,
a gun is a lot easier.

17:27.755 --> 17:30.424
They didn't just want her dead.
They wanted her terrified.

17:30.424 --> 17:32.260
[ Cellphone chimes ]

17:32.260 --> 17:34.345
Hold on. I just got video
footage from Pam's house.

17:41.269 --> 17:43.020
Can't see his face.

17:45.314 --> 17:48.025
Alright. The garage camera's
triggered 7 minutes later.

17:51.654 --> 17:53.531
Is there
any other angle?

17:53.531 --> 17:54.865
No, that's it.

17:54.865 --> 17:56.617
Wait, wait.
Go back real quick.

17:58.077 --> 18:00.121
Yeah. I feel like
she recognizes him.

18:00.121 --> 18:01.581
Yeah, she doesn't
seem scared.

18:01.581 --> 18:05.209
Whoever he is,
she wasn't expecting trouble.

18:05.209 --> 18:08.087
Alright, mother's name is
Marianne Winfield.

18:08.087 --> 18:10.798
62, works in PR,
and...

18:10.798 --> 18:13.718
man, she's about to receive
the worst news of her life.

18:15.303 --> 18:16.887
Alright.
I'll do the talking.

18:16.887 --> 18:18.973
It's better
if only one of us speaks.

18:18.973 --> 18:20.516
That way,
the person can focus

18:20.516 --> 18:21.726
a little easier
on what we're telling them.

18:21.726 --> 18:23.394
Well, I can do it.

18:23.394 --> 18:25.062
You sure?

18:25.062 --> 18:27.607
I have to make my first
death notification sometime.

18:27.607 --> 18:30.484
Might as well be today.

18:30.484 --> 18:32.320
Okay.

18:32.320 --> 18:34.196
Don't speak
in euphemisms.

18:34.196 --> 18:36.907
No "passed on"
or "in a better place."

18:36.907 --> 18:39.201
Just be direct.

18:39.201 --> 18:40.828
"We have bad news.

18:40.828 --> 18:43.456
Your daughter Pam was killed
today in an explosion."

18:43.456 --> 18:45.458
You know, when the police
told my mom

18:45.458 --> 18:48.919
that they'd recovered my sister,
they said, "We found her."

18:48.919 --> 18:51.464
And for a second,
we thought...

18:52.882 --> 18:54.759
So you understand
how important this is.

18:54.759 --> 18:57.094
Yeah. I do.

18:57.094 --> 18:58.679
Okay.

18:58.679 --> 19:04.477
♪♪

19:04.477 --> 19:06.687
[ Murmuring ] Celina Juarez.
This is Officer John Nolan.

19:06.687 --> 19:14.153
♪♪

19:14.153 --> 19:21.619
♪♪

19:21.619 --> 19:29.293
♪♪

19:29.293 --> 19:31.212
Lucy: That poor woman.

19:31.212 --> 19:33.923
The last moments of her life
must have been agony,

19:33.923 --> 19:35.716
just wondering if the bomb
was gonna go off,

19:35.716 --> 19:37.176
praying it wouldn't.

19:37.176 --> 19:38.928
I'm guessing
that was the point.

19:38.928 --> 19:41.263
No way someone goes through
that much trouble of building

19:41.263 --> 19:43.724
something like that unless they
want to terrorize their victim.

19:43.724 --> 19:44.767
Yeah.

19:44.767 --> 19:48.104
[ Cellphone rings ]

19:48.104 --> 19:49.313
Hey.

19:49.313 --> 19:50.690
I saw the news.
Are you okay?

19:50.690 --> 19:52.817
Yeah, I'm fine,
but it's crazy out here.

19:52.817 --> 19:55.986
Okay. Look, if you
don't have time, I get it.

19:55.986 --> 19:57.655
But a Realtor friend of mine
just slipped me a listing.

19:57.655 --> 19:59.615
<i>It hasn't been</i>
<i>posted online yet.</i>

19:59.615 --> 20:01.867
So, uh, if you like it,
I think we should move on it.

20:01.867 --> 20:04.036
Wow. Um, okay.

20:04.036 --> 20:07.206
Chen, chat with your boyfriend
on your own time.

20:07.206 --> 20:09.709
He's in a mood.
I'll let you go.

20:09.709 --> 20:11.919
Just text me and let me know
what you think?

20:11.919 --> 20:13.170
Yeah, I-I'll do that.

20:16.549 --> 20:17.883
Thanks.

20:20.219 --> 20:22.888
Pam Winfield was an in-house
counsel at Sunvale Oil

20:22.888 --> 20:24.265
for the past five years.

20:24.265 --> 20:26.350
Security e-mailed me
a list of people

20:26.350 --> 20:28.185
who sent threatening letters
to the company.

20:28.185 --> 20:31.814
The first guy lives
over on Orange Grove.

20:31.814 --> 20:33.232
Alright, let's go
pay him a visit.

20:33.232 --> 20:36.277
How's the Tar Pits
case going?

20:36.277 --> 20:38.654
I haven't been
thinking about it.

20:38.654 --> 20:40.906
After what happened,
it seems kind of silly.

20:40.906 --> 20:43.200
Part of being a detective
is juggling cases,

20:43.200 --> 20:46.370
switching between
wildly different gears.

20:46.370 --> 20:50.249
Okay. Um...

20:50.249 --> 20:53.210
Okay. We have the boyfriend.
We have the artifacts broker.

20:53.210 --> 20:55.671
Both have motive
to kill the guard.

20:55.671 --> 20:57.882
I-I feel like I need to know
more about the theft.

20:57.882 --> 21:00.885
Like, how did she get roped up
in this in the first place?

21:00.885 --> 21:02.928
Is that
a fourth question?

21:02.928 --> 21:05.347
Yes. Did the guard
take the job at the museum

21:05.347 --> 21:07.016
in order to gain access
to the artifacts?

21:07.016 --> 21:09.185
It's hard to say,
but we <i>do</i> know

21:09.185 --> 21:10.770
that her
black-market contact

21:10.770 --> 21:13.063
was also her
high-school sweetheart.

21:13.063 --> 21:15.566
<i>Another</i> love interest?
[ Pen clicks ]

21:15.566 --> 21:17.443
Okay.
Now we're getting somewhere.

21:24.617 --> 21:27.328
This is a lot.

21:27.328 --> 21:30.581
Watching her die,
having to tell her mother.

21:30.581 --> 21:33.417
It's more than anyone should
have to deal with in a day.

21:33.417 --> 21:35.544
But our shift
isn't over yet.

21:35.544 --> 21:37.838
I know. I'm okay.

21:39.965 --> 21:42.802
[ Cellphone rings ]

21:42.802 --> 21:44.887
Hey. Where are you?

21:44.887 --> 21:46.388
I'm under the house.

21:46.388 --> 21:48.015
Why?

21:48.015 --> 21:51.268
I keep hearing this noise,
and it's driving me crazy.

21:51.268 --> 21:53.229
And you thought
it would be a good idea

21:53.229 --> 21:54.897
to go under there
by yourself?

21:54.897 --> 21:56.315
That's why
I FaceTimed you.

21:56.315 --> 21:58.609
That's not the same.
It's not --

21:58.609 --> 22:00.861
Wait. What is that?

22:00.861 --> 22:02.029
What is what?
Aah!

22:02.029 --> 22:03.072
Bailey?

22:04.490 --> 22:06.075
Bailey?! What is what?!
Bailey!

22:06.075 --> 22:09.411
Sorry. False alarm.
It's just this guy.

22:09.411 --> 22:11.622
Oh, God!

22:11.622 --> 22:13.082
What is <i>that</i>
doing under there?

22:13.082 --> 22:16.210
I don't know.
Should I move it?
Yeah.

22:16.210 --> 22:19.088
No! No! Not till
you consult an exorcist.

22:24.260 --> 22:26.679
Look, if you don't want to
move in, just tell Chris that.

22:26.679 --> 22:28.472
That's...

22:28.472 --> 22:30.891
The question is,
<i>why</i> don't I want to move in?

22:30.891 --> 22:33.185
I don't get what the problem is.
I mean, Chris is great.

22:33.185 --> 22:35.896
We're great together.
We never fight.

22:35.896 --> 22:38.816
Maybe that's the problem.

22:38.816 --> 22:40.734
Oh, you think we should be like
that couple from this morning?

22:40.734 --> 22:42.695
No, I'm not saying that,
but -- No.

22:42.695 --> 22:44.238
But do you guys not fight

22:44.238 --> 22:46.282
because you don't
disagree on things,

22:46.282 --> 22:48.701
or because you don't think
it's worth the bother?

22:52.621 --> 22:54.248
Lucy.
Yeah?

22:54.248 --> 22:57.084
You deserve someone
who's worth the effort.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.590
[ Engine revs ]

23:02.590 --> 23:04.425
[ Tires screech ]

23:04.425 --> 23:05.801
What was that?

23:05.801 --> 23:07.428
[ Siren wails ]

23:10.139 --> 23:10.890
He--

23:10.890 --> 23:14.435
♪♪

23:14.435 --> 23:17.187
Control, 7-Adam-100.
There is a second bomb.

23:17.187 --> 23:18.314
Repeat.
There's a second bomb.

23:24.570 --> 23:26.739
What's your name?!
Lucy: Hey!
[ Grunts ]at's your name?

23:26.739 --> 23:29.575
[ Siren wailing ]

23:29.575 --> 23:30.993
[ Cellphone rings ]
Get me as close
as you can, okay?

23:30.993 --> 23:31.785
Tim: Right.

23:32.870 --> 23:34.538
Hey. Reach out.

23:34.538 --> 23:35.706
[ Grunts ]

23:35.706 --> 23:37.458
Reach out. Reach out.
Okay.

23:40.169 --> 23:42.463
Can you get closer?
Yeah.

23:42.463 --> 23:43.672
Here, here, here.

23:43.672 --> 23:44.673
Got it!

23:44.673 --> 23:47.426
♪♪

23:47.426 --> 23:49.511
Hi. I'm Lucy.

23:49.511 --> 23:51.722
Hi. H-He told me
to keep driving.

23:51.722 --> 23:54.141
I don't want to die!

23:54.141 --> 23:57.102
Sir, we're here to help you.
What's your name?

23:57.102 --> 23:58.437
Creighton.
Creighton Mitchell.

23:58.437 --> 24:00.064
Okay. Creighton,
we're gonna try

24:00.064 --> 24:01.607
and get you to drive
somewhere safe.

24:01.607 --> 24:03.317
You think
you can do that?

24:03.317 --> 24:05.194
[ Breathlessly ]
I can't breathe.

24:05.194 --> 24:07.780
I feel like I'm dying.
I think I'm dying.

24:07.780 --> 24:09.698
Creighton, you're probably
having a panic attack right now.

24:09.698 --> 24:11.533
I just need you
to try and stay calm.

24:11.533 --> 24:14.578
Maybe turn on the radio
for some music?

24:14.578 --> 24:16.664
Woman: [ On radio ]
<i>A woman is dead today</i>

24:16.664 --> 24:18.582
<i>after an unknown assailant</i>
<i>apparently strapped</i>

24:18.582 --> 24:20.501
<i>an explosive device</i>
<i>to her neck.</i>

24:20.501 --> 24:22.586
Oh, my God!
This happened to somebody else?!

24:22.586 --> 24:23.337
And she's dead?!

24:23.337 --> 24:24.296
Creighton,
listen to me.

24:24.296 --> 24:25.798
That is not gonna be you,
okay?

24:25.798 --> 24:27.967
You can bet your ass
this isn't gonna be me!

24:27.967 --> 24:32.638
♪♪

24:32.638 --> 24:33.764
Creighton!

24:33.764 --> 24:36.141
[ Tires screech ]

24:36.141 --> 24:37.226
♪♪

24:37.226 --> 24:38.477
Creighton, stop!

24:38.477 --> 24:40.896
<i>You could detonate</i>
<i>the device!</i>

24:40.896 --> 24:42.272
I'm not just gonna wait
for this thing

24:42.272 --> 24:44.650
to blow my head off!

24:44.650 --> 24:46.402
<i>Everyone, back up!</i>
<i>Get inside the house!</i>
<i>There's a bomb!</i>

24:46.402 --> 24:49.029
<i>Back up!</i>
<i>Clear it out! Clear off</i>
<i>the sidewalk! Let's go!</i>

24:49.029 --> 24:50.656
[ <i>Creighton grunting</i> ]

24:50.656 --> 24:52.199
♪♪

24:52.199 --> 24:54.159
[ Grunting ]

24:54.159 --> 24:55.411
[ Clang ]
Ow!

24:55.411 --> 24:56.954
[ Breathing heavily ]

24:56.954 --> 25:00.040
I'm alive!
[ Laughs ]

25:00.040 --> 25:02.292
♪♪

25:02.292 --> 25:04.003
[ Whirring,
indistinct radio chatter ]

25:05.921 --> 25:07.464
Yeah, so the bomb
was on a timer.

25:07.464 --> 25:09.008
He had 3 minutes left.

25:09.008 --> 25:10.509
<i>It's a good thing he bailed</i>
<i>when he did.</i>

25:10.509 --> 25:12.219
<i>We would have never</i>
<i>made it on time.</i>

25:12.219 --> 25:13.637
<i>How long</i>
<i>did he have total?</i>

25:13.637 --> 25:15.097
<i>Couldn't tell</i>
<i>from the device,</i>

25:15.097 --> 25:16.890
<i>but as long as he was driving</i>
<i>plus 3 minutes.</i>

25:16.890 --> 25:19.226
Okay, thanks. Bye.

25:19.226 --> 25:21.186
What time was the device
activated?

25:21.186 --> 25:23.856
Uh, I don't know.
Uh, a while?

25:23.856 --> 25:25.941
He activated it right before
he put me in the car.

25:25.941 --> 25:28.068
Alright, we'll get the GPS
off your car.

25:28.068 --> 25:30.070
Lucy: What exactly can you
remember from this morning?

25:30.070 --> 25:31.780
<i>I was going to work.</i>

25:31.780 --> 25:34.450
<i>I-I-I heard a knock at the door</i>
<i>and when I answered it,</i>

25:34.450 --> 25:37.036
<i>Richard was standing there</i>
<i>with a collar and a gun.</i>

25:37.036 --> 25:39.413
Richard?
Dormer.
Richard Dormer.

25:39.413 --> 25:41.749
I-I used to work with
his sister at Sunvale.

25:41.749 --> 25:44.126
Oh. Sunvale Oil?

25:44.126 --> 25:45.961
Did you know
Pam Winfield?

25:45.961 --> 25:48.714
<i>Yeah. Why?</i>

25:48.714 --> 25:50.924
<i>The woman they were</i>
<i>talking about on</i>
<i>the radio this morning,</i>

25:50.924 --> 25:51.967
<i>uh, that was Pam.</i>

25:51.967 --> 25:53.844
<i>What?!</i>

25:53.844 --> 25:57.431
<i>Yeah. I'm sorry.</i>
<i>Were you close?</i>

25:57.431 --> 25:58.849
<i>I-I-I mean,</i>
<i>I-I worked with her.</i>

25:58.849 --> 26:01.018
<i>Wh-What is this?</i>
<i>What's going on?</i>

26:01.018 --> 26:04.313
<i>That's what we're trying</i>
<i>to figure out here.</i>

26:04.313 --> 26:05.981
<i>What did Richard</i>
<i>say to you?</i>

26:05.981 --> 26:07.608
<i>He told me if -- if I didn't</i>
<i>put the collar on,</i>

26:07.608 --> 26:08.734
<i>he'd kill me.</i>

26:08.734 --> 26:10.778
<i>And he didn't</i>
<i>give you any reason?</i>

26:10.778 --> 26:12.529
[ <i>Sighs</i> ]
<i>It was all so fast.</i>

26:12.529 --> 26:14.114
<i>I-I-I don't know.</i>
<i>I don't know.</i>

26:14.114 --> 26:15.616
Uh, do you have
his sister's number?

26:15.616 --> 26:17.493
She might be able
to give us some insight.

26:17.493 --> 26:20.079
<i>No, no.</i>
<i>She's -- She's dead.</i>

26:22.081 --> 26:23.082
Do you know
what happened?

26:26.043 --> 26:27.753
<i>We...</i>
[ <i>Sighs</i> ]

26:27.753 --> 26:29.880
<i>We sent her abroad</i>
<i>to handle a deal,</i>

26:29.880 --> 26:34.093
<i>and she was kidnapped</i>
<i>and...she was killed.</i>

26:36.470 --> 26:38.055
How were you and Pam
involved?

26:38.055 --> 26:40.724
<i>It was our call,</i>

26:40.724 --> 26:42.184
<i>whether or not</i>
<i>to pay the ransom.</i>

26:42.184 --> 26:44.144
<i>I mean -- And we were</i>
<i>going to, I-I swear.</i>

26:44.144 --> 26:45.771
But, you know,
you negotiate these things.

26:45.771 --> 26:48.607
You -- It's how you do it.
They expect you to do it.

26:48.607 --> 26:52.361
But these guys, they panicked
or -- I don't know.

26:52.361 --> 26:56.448
<i>All I know is...</i>
<i>she died over there.</i>

26:57.699 --> 26:59.701
7-Adam-15, I need you
to pick up Richard Dormer.

26:59.701 --> 27:02.371
Proceed with extreme caution.
He might be our bomber.

27:02.371 --> 27:04.414
[ Engine revs ]

27:04.414 --> 27:06.291
Stay alert.
Watch his hands.

27:06.291 --> 27:07.668
[ Tires screech ]

27:09.503 --> 27:11.880
Richard Dormer, keep your hands
where I can see them!

27:11.880 --> 27:13.882
Is this all for me?

27:13.882 --> 27:15.217
Turn around.
Get on the ground.

27:15.217 --> 27:17.553
<i>I'm unarmed.</i>
<i>I know how this ends.</i>

27:17.553 --> 27:19.263
I don't mind
going to prison.

27:19.263 --> 27:21.890
Turn around and get
on the ground, now.

27:21.890 --> 27:24.768
[ Handcuffs rattle ]

27:24.768 --> 27:26.311
Lopez: We need the bomb squad
to do a search

27:26.311 --> 27:27.813
before we process
the house.

27:27.813 --> 27:30.899
<i>You don't have to be afraid.</i>
<i>The explosives are gone.</i>

27:30.899 --> 27:32.609
The third bomb's
already out there.

27:32.609 --> 27:35.070
♪♪

27:35.070 --> 27:37.072
Harper: <i>Apparently there were</i>
<i>three people who signed off</i>

27:37.072 --> 27:38.782
on negotiating rather
than paying the ransom --

27:38.782 --> 27:40.117
Pam, Creighton,

27:40.117 --> 27:42.452
and Henri Parsons,
the company CEO.

27:42.452 --> 27:44.621
You have a phone number?
Yes, but he is not answering.

27:44.621 --> 27:47.332
Lopez is getting authorization
to track it as we speak.

27:47.332 --> 27:48.709
Alright, well,
based on Creighton's GPS,

27:48.709 --> 27:50.460
he had 43 minutes
from the time

27:50.460 --> 27:51.837
<i>the bomb was activated</i>
<i>until it was detonated.</i>

27:51.837 --> 27:53.797
Why 43 minutes?

27:53.797 --> 27:55.424
You're the detective.

27:55.424 --> 27:57.759
Okay. Henri drives
a black BMW 5 Series,

27:57.759 --> 27:59.011
and he lives
in Cheviot Hills.

27:59.011 --> 28:00.762
We could head up there,
drive a grid.

28:00.762 --> 28:02.014
<i>It's a start.</i>

28:03.849 --> 28:06.894
Okay. I guess we should pick up
a pair of garden shears.

28:06.894 --> 28:09.021
[ Scoffs ] Don't think we can
rely on that working again.

28:09.021 --> 28:10.272
Yeah.

28:10.272 --> 28:12.608
[ Cellphone chimes ]

28:12.608 --> 28:13.901
[ Scoffs ]

28:13.901 --> 28:15.652
More home listings?

28:15.652 --> 28:16.904
Yeah.

28:16.904 --> 28:18.280
Oh, you've
gotta be kidding me.

28:18.280 --> 28:21.366
This one's in Monrovia.
Who wants to live in Monrovia?

28:21.366 --> 28:23.619
It looks like Chris does.

28:29.833 --> 28:30.626
Do you love him?

28:36.340 --> 28:38.926
I mean, we haven't even
been dating that long.

28:38.926 --> 28:39.801
It's not...

28:47.392 --> 28:48.644
He loves you.

28:48.644 --> 28:50.812
I know.

28:50.812 --> 28:53.607
I know, and I feel like
I should love him back.

28:53.607 --> 28:55.651
He's so great
in so many different ways.

28:55.651 --> 28:57.861
It's just...

28:57.861 --> 28:59.821
He's just not...

29:11.750 --> 29:14.461
You know, you killed
an innocent woman today.

29:14.461 --> 29:15.963
There was nothing innocent

29:15.963 --> 29:17.255
about Pam Winfield.

29:17.255 --> 29:19.841
She got what she deserved.

29:19.841 --> 29:23.428
She experienced exactly what
she forced my sister

29:23.428 --> 29:25.389
to experience --

29:25.389 --> 29:30.102
43 minutes of terror
and then darkness.

29:30.102 --> 29:31.561
What do you mean?

29:31.561 --> 29:34.398
Where she was abducted,
where they held her,

29:34.398 --> 29:36.233
and where she died.

29:36.233 --> 29:38.485
It took 43 minutes

29:38.485 --> 29:40.153
to drive her out to the desert

29:40.153 --> 29:41.530
to be executed.

29:43.323 --> 29:45.993
<i>Kidnappers</i> killed
your sister.

29:45.993 --> 29:47.953
It wasn't Pam's fault

29:47.953 --> 29:49.621
or Creighton's fault
or Henri's!

29:49.621 --> 29:51.665
She trusted them!

29:51.665 --> 29:53.500
She believed their promises

29:53.500 --> 29:56.712
that if anything happened,
they would have her back!

29:56.712 --> 29:58.130
[ Scoffs ]

29:58.130 --> 30:01.508
♪♪

30:01.508 --> 30:04.845
You know, every single person
in that company is guilty.

30:04.845 --> 30:06.430
Every single one.

30:06.430 --> 30:08.557
They all knew
she was taken,

30:08.557 --> 30:10.475
and not one person
fought for her.

30:10.475 --> 30:12.144
Not one.

30:12.144 --> 30:13.645
People she worked with
for years

30:13.645 --> 30:16.690
just sat on their hands
and let her die.

30:18.734 --> 30:20.861
Henri's not just
driving around randomly

30:20.861 --> 30:21.903
like the others,
is he?

30:21.903 --> 30:27.659
♪♪

30:27.659 --> 30:29.369
Now, I've been assuming
foul play,

30:29.369 --> 30:32.080
but maybe the victim
committed suicide

30:32.080 --> 30:35.792
or got drunk
and had an accident.

30:35.792 --> 30:38.628
Was there a question in there?
You've only got one more.

30:40.380 --> 30:42.924
No. No, there's not.

30:42.924 --> 30:45.093
[ Cellphone rings ]

30:45.093 --> 30:46.595
Nolan,
what do we got?

30:46.595 --> 30:49.347
The third victim isn't just
randomly driving around.

30:49.347 --> 30:51.308
He's on his way
to Sunvale Oil offices.

30:51.308 --> 30:53.268
The third bomb's gonna
take out the whole company.

31:01.485 --> 31:03.737
♪♪

31:03.737 --> 31:05.155
[ Engine revs ]

31:05.155 --> 31:06.448
[ Tires screech ]

31:06.448 --> 31:07.657
Stay with him.

31:07.657 --> 31:08.950
Yeah.

31:08.950 --> 31:12.746
[ Employees screaming ]

31:12.746 --> 31:14.414
Nolan:
<i>Keep moving. Keep moving.</i>

31:14.414 --> 31:15.665
<i>The far side of</i>
<i>the parking lot. Keep --</i>

31:15.665 --> 31:19.795
♪♪

31:19.795 --> 31:22.047
<i>Control, 7-Adam-15.</i>
<i>I've located our third victim.</i>

31:22.047 --> 31:24.257
<i>Corporate offices, Sunvale Oil.</i>
<i>He's confirmed on site.</i>

31:24.257 --> 31:28.720
♪♪

31:28.720 --> 31:31.139
Celina: <i>Nolan's inside</i>
<i>with the bomb.</i>

31:31.139 --> 31:32.390
We need to clear
the building.

31:32.390 --> 31:41.274
♪♪

31:41.274 --> 31:42.818
We need you to clear out.
Move.

31:42.818 --> 31:44.444
Everyone, listen up!

31:44.444 --> 31:46.530
We have a credible threat
at this location!

31:46.530 --> 31:48.698
<i>I need everyone</i>
<i>to move with purpose!</i>

31:48.698 --> 31:50.075
Aaron: <i>Come on. Everybody</i>
<i>move quickly but stay calm.</i>

31:50.075 --> 31:51.451
Let's go. This way.
Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

31:51.451 --> 31:52.869
Let's spread out and make sure
there are no stragglers.

31:52.869 --> 31:54.746
♪♪

31:54.746 --> 31:58.125
Mr. Parsons. Mr. Parsons.
Hey. I'm John Nolan.

31:58.125 --> 32:00.418
<i>Help me.</i>
<i>Please help me.</i>

32:00.418 --> 32:02.587
That's why I'm here.
That's why -- What's this?

32:02.587 --> 32:05.090
He -- He told me
to stream an apology.

32:05.090 --> 32:07.134
Okay. First, we're gonna get
all these people out of here.

32:07.134 --> 32:08.760
<i>Folks, come on.</i>
<i>We're gonna move outside.</i>

32:08.760 --> 32:10.971
No. He told me
not to let them go.

32:10.971 --> 32:12.806
He said he'd kill me
if they left.

32:12.806 --> 32:15.433
<i>Relax. Okay? No -- You've been</i>
<i>told a lie. Okay, folks?</i>

32:15.433 --> 32:18.145
The bomber is right now
outside in my car.

32:18.145 --> 32:21.773
I can guarantee he does not have
a remote trigger with him.

32:21.773 --> 32:23.150
This bomb is on a timer.

32:23.150 --> 32:24.192
<i>You're sure?</i>

32:24.192 --> 32:25.944
<i>100%.</i>
<i>Nice and safe, guys.</i>

32:25.944 --> 32:26.695
<i>Everyone move outside.</i>

32:26.695 --> 32:27.779
Downstairs.

32:27.779 --> 32:28.738
The far side
of the parking lot

32:28.738 --> 32:29.656
as fast as you can,
alright?

32:29.656 --> 32:31.533
Quick and safe.

32:31.533 --> 32:33.326
<i>How long ago did he put</i>
<i>this bomb on your neck?</i>

32:33.326 --> 32:34.870
<i>Huh? Uh...</i>
<i>You gotta think, okay?</i>

32:34.870 --> 32:37.372
<i>The timer is for 43 minutes,</i>
<i>so you have to think.</i>

32:37.372 --> 32:39.541
How long ago did he put this
on your neck?

32:39.541 --> 32:40.584
Uh...uh...

32:40.584 --> 32:42.711
More than a half-hour.

32:42.711 --> 32:44.462
Uh, maybe 40 minutes?

32:44.462 --> 32:47.799
Okay. That's...not great.
It could be worse.

32:47.799 --> 32:50.760
<i>Everyone out!</i>
<i>Come on, ladies. Move, move!</i>

32:50.760 --> 32:52.304
What about me?

32:52.304 --> 32:55.765
You and I, we're gonna
focus on this bomb, okay?

32:55.765 --> 32:57.726
<i>Let's take a look here,</i>
<i>see what we've got, alright?</i>

32:57.726 --> 32:59.519
<i>Stay nice and calm</i>
<i>for me.</i>

32:59.519 --> 33:02.022
Tell me how to
disarm the bomb.

33:02.022 --> 33:03.356
No.

33:03.356 --> 33:05.025
My T. O. is up there,

33:05.025 --> 33:07.360
and he's not gonna leave
someone who is scared and alone.

33:07.360 --> 33:09.362
If that bomb goes off,
you're killing him, too.

33:09.362 --> 33:11.364
Yeah, well, he's making
a choice to stay.

33:11.364 --> 33:13.074
And you're making a choice
to kill people.

33:13.074 --> 33:15.368
There have to be
consequences!

33:15.368 --> 33:18.747
My sister is dead.
They need to pay.

33:18.747 --> 33:21.374
Look, I get it.
Nolan: <i>This is the hinge point.</i>

33:21.374 --> 33:24.169
My little sister was taken away
from me a long time ago,

33:24.169 --> 33:25.295
and I spent
most of my life

33:25.295 --> 33:26.838
thinking of all
the different ways

33:26.838 --> 33:28.465
I would hurt
the person responsible.

33:28.465 --> 33:31.259
But all that hate
just ate away at me

33:31.259 --> 33:33.303
until I didn't
recognize myself.

33:33.303 --> 33:35.722
Your sister
wouldn't want this.

33:35.722 --> 33:37.724
<i>Okay.</i>

33:37.724 --> 33:40.435
<i>This is entirely smooth.</i>
<i>I can't get in from the back.</i>

33:40.435 --> 33:43.230
I want my apology.

33:43.230 --> 33:45.523
I want him to admit
what he did

33:45.523 --> 33:47.776
for the whole world
to hear.

33:47.776 --> 33:48.818
[ Breathing heavily ]
Where does this go?

33:48.818 --> 33:50.570
Is the bomb squad coming?

33:50.570 --> 33:52.197
Yeah, any minute now.

33:52.197 --> 33:53.573
I only have a couple
of those left.

33:53.573 --> 33:54.950
"We."

33:54.950 --> 33:56.701
I'm staying with you
till we figure this out.

33:56.701 --> 33:58.870
♪♪

33:58.870 --> 34:00.330
<i>The floor is clear.</i>

34:00.330 --> 34:02.165
<i>We should go.</i>
<i>The bomb squad is almost here.</i>

34:03.667 --> 34:04.626
<i>John?</i>

34:04.626 --> 34:06.336
<i>Go.</i>

34:06.336 --> 34:08.797
<i>You don't</i>
<i>have to do this.</i>

34:08.797 --> 34:10.674
<i>Yes, I do.</i>

34:10.674 --> 34:12.217
<i>Harper, go.</i>

34:12.217 --> 34:15.345
♪♪

34:15.345 --> 34:16.721
[ Siren wails ]

34:16.721 --> 34:17.847
[ Cellphone dials ]

34:17.847 --> 34:19.432
[ <i>Cellphone ringing</i> ]

34:19.432 --> 34:22.102
♪♪

34:22.102 --> 34:23.687
Nolan:
<i>Not a good time.</i>

34:23.687 --> 34:25.814
Richard says he'll tell us
how to disarm the bomb

34:25.814 --> 34:27.315
if Parson just admits
what he did.

34:27.315 --> 34:30.277
I didn't do anything.
I was negotiating.

34:30.277 --> 34:33.947
Hey. Your semantics are
gonna get us both killed.

34:33.947 --> 34:36.324
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:36.324 --> 34:37.701
I'm sorry.

34:37.701 --> 34:40.620
<i>We let her die.</i>
<i>It was my fault.</i>

34:40.620 --> 34:42.122
I made the call.

34:42.122 --> 34:45.000
Susan Dormer is dead
because of me.

34:46.376 --> 34:47.711
[ Sighs ]

34:51.172 --> 34:54.801
There's two wires in the back,
a red and a green one.

34:54.801 --> 34:57.304
Cut the green wire.

35:00.181 --> 35:01.224
[ Knife clicks ]

35:03.518 --> 35:06.479
♪♪

35:06.479 --> 35:08.898
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

35:08.898 --> 35:09.941
He's lying.

35:09.941 --> 35:11.484
What?

35:11.484 --> 35:13.653
He doesn't want an apology.
He wants Parsons dead.

35:13.653 --> 35:14.487
Cut the red one.

35:14.487 --> 35:22.037
♪♪

35:22.037 --> 35:23.246
Are you sure?

35:23.246 --> 35:24.664
Yes.

35:24.664 --> 35:25.999
♪♪

35:25.999 --> 35:26.791
[ <i>Bomb powering down</i> ]

35:28.168 --> 35:29.586
[ Breathing shakily ]

35:29.586 --> 35:32.297
Okay. Nice and easy.

35:32.297 --> 35:37.177
♪♪

35:37.177 --> 35:38.053
[ Gasps ]

35:42.307 --> 35:46.353
Nolan: <i>Thank you.</i>
<i>And...thank</i> you.

35:46.353 --> 35:47.937
<i>You saved my life today.</i>

35:47.937 --> 35:51.566
<i>That kind of insight</i>
<i>in a rookie is...remarkable.</i>

35:53.401 --> 35:54.736
[ Camera beeps ]

35:54.736 --> 35:56.196
You know, I...

35:56.196 --> 35:58.698
I wouldn't be
making so much progress

35:58.698 --> 36:00.116
without
such a great T. O.

36:01.868 --> 36:03.161
Thank you again.

36:03.161 --> 36:05.080
You know,
I wouldn't mind at all

36:05.080 --> 36:08.166
if you repeated that
in front of Sgt. Grey.

36:08.166 --> 36:11.169
Just saying, repeating things
is good in general.

36:11.169 --> 36:13.630
Sgt. Grey, imagine --
Have you seen "Inception"?

36:13.630 --> 36:15.256
I'll walk you through it.

36:15.256 --> 36:18.301
Okay, so, I think
I solved your case.

36:18.301 --> 36:20.011
You have one more question
you could ask.

36:20.011 --> 36:21.346
Nope.
Don't need it.

36:21.346 --> 36:24.432
Hmm. Cocky.
Alright, let's hear it.

36:24.432 --> 36:26.559
Okay, so, the victim was dating
one of the scientists

36:26.559 --> 36:28.353
who worked at the Tar Pits,
right?

36:28.353 --> 36:30.730
And she was part
of a smuggling ring

36:30.730 --> 36:32.524
that sold artifacts
on the black market.

36:32.524 --> 36:35.819
So, was it
a jealous lover

36:35.819 --> 36:38.238
or a criminal enterprise
gone wrong?

36:39.948 --> 36:41.866
Actually, it was both.

36:41.866 --> 36:44.619
She was sleeping with both
the smuggler and the scientist,

36:44.619 --> 36:47.455
and they found out
and they killed her together.

36:49.332 --> 36:52.669
I think you have a <i>long</i> road
to detective, Officer Thorsen.

36:52.669 --> 36:54.462
Wait.
Was I at least close?

36:54.462 --> 36:56.172
You had
five questions.

36:56.172 --> 36:57.507
Right.

36:57.507 --> 37:00.343
And you never asked
the <i>age</i> of the remains.

37:00.343 --> 37:02.303
Well, no, no, no.
The -- The -- The file said

37:02.303 --> 37:04.097
that she was 32
when she went missing.

37:04.097 --> 37:07.434
Right, but the bone
was thousands of years old.

37:07.434 --> 37:09.185
You see, the Tar Pits
are constantly

37:09.185 --> 37:10.979
turning up
ancient remains.

37:10.979 --> 37:13.022
So in -- in this case,

37:13.022 --> 37:15.817
the killer was
a-a saber-toothed tiger.

37:17.986 --> 37:19.362
Wait. What happened
to the missing guard?

37:19.362 --> 37:22.699
Oh, she was found
in Mexico a year later.

37:22.699 --> 37:25.618
You see, you assumed
that there was a connection

37:25.618 --> 37:28.830
between the female remains
and the missing woman.
Yeah.

37:28.830 --> 37:32.500
First rule of investigation --
Don't make assumptions.

37:32.500 --> 37:37.172
♪♪

37:38.923 --> 37:40.759
[ Grunts ]

37:40.759 --> 37:41.968
Oh.

37:45.180 --> 37:47.807
Looks like a toy store
threw up in our house.

37:47.807 --> 37:49.350
Well, Jack got
two shots today.

37:49.350 --> 37:51.770
I didn't want him to
associate me with needles.

37:51.770 --> 37:53.563
Did he cry?

37:53.563 --> 37:55.398
No.

37:55.398 --> 37:57.776
Did <i>you</i> cry?
That's irrelevant.

37:57.776 --> 38:01.154
Not according to
our living room, it's not.

38:01.154 --> 38:03.907
Doesn't Jack already have
a basketball hoop?

38:03.907 --> 38:07.076
Well, yeah, but now
he's got an outside one

38:07.076 --> 38:08.995
<i>and</i> an inside one...

38:08.995 --> 38:10.163
[ Sighs ]

38:14.751 --> 38:17.796
[ Chuckles ]
[ Buzzes lips ] Ohh.

38:17.796 --> 38:20.465
I don't know how you deal with
watching him get shots so often.

38:20.465 --> 38:23.968
Well, I know
it's for his own good.

38:23.968 --> 38:27.180
I know I have to be tough
to show him how to be tough.

38:29.265 --> 38:31.893
And...I fill him full of
ice cream right after.

38:33.061 --> 38:35.230
Oh, you didn't tell me
<i>that</i> trick.

38:37.273 --> 38:39.442
Because you want
to be his favorite.

38:39.442 --> 38:41.653
I'm already his favorite.
[ Laughs ]

38:41.653 --> 38:45.073
♪ It's the epilogue ♪

38:45.073 --> 38:47.826
♪ Of the sequel to the first ♪

38:47.826 --> 38:49.494
Welcome home!
[ Door closes ]

38:49.494 --> 38:52.205
Thank you for cleaning off
all those cobwebs

38:52.205 --> 38:55.208
and clown...
before I got home.

38:55.208 --> 38:56.793
Can never clean that clown
off my mind, though.

38:56.793 --> 38:58.253
Ugh.
Where is he now?

38:58.253 --> 38:59.504
Outside.
Where he belongs.

38:59.504 --> 39:00.421
Mm-hmm.

39:00.421 --> 39:02.215
Oh, geez!

39:02.215 --> 39:04.592
[ Laughs ]
I couldn't help myself.

39:04.592 --> 39:06.594
♪ Where she was
born and raised ♪

39:06.594 --> 39:08.680
We are gonna take it
outside to burn.

39:08.680 --> 39:11.015
The only way to kill
this kind of evil is by fire.

39:11.015 --> 39:12.851
Nolan:
You got that right.

39:12.851 --> 39:15.645
So, if it was just a doll,
what was making the noise?

39:15.645 --> 39:19.649
Well, when I got off the phone,
I found something else.

39:21.192 --> 39:23.486
A puppy!
Oh.

39:23.486 --> 39:26.739
This little guy was making
all that ruckus.

39:26.739 --> 39:27.615
Can we keep him?

39:27.615 --> 39:29.659
No.
I'll just give him a bath.

39:29.659 --> 39:32.787
No, I mean,
that's -- that's not a puppy.

39:32.787 --> 39:34.414
That's a coyote.

39:34.414 --> 39:37.584
♪ 'Cause you feel safe
in the light ♪

39:37.584 --> 39:39.669
How did you get him
in a crate?

39:39.669 --> 39:45.842
♪♪

39:45.842 --> 39:47.594
Hey. We need to talk.

39:48.845 --> 39:50.430
Let me guess.

39:50.430 --> 39:52.056
Chris wants to buy
a house in Chatsworth?

39:52.056 --> 39:54.350
No.
[ Scoffs ]

39:54.350 --> 39:58.605
Look, this clearly
isn't working out.

39:58.605 --> 40:01.190
I don't know why
you won't just admit it.

40:01.190 --> 40:03.568
Unless -- Is it guilt?

40:03.568 --> 40:05.320
Is it because of
what Rosalind did to him?

40:05.320 --> 40:07.196
Oh, like I'm the only one
that's stayed too long

40:07.196 --> 40:08.948
when things
aren't working.

40:08.948 --> 40:10.575
You dated
a lifeguard.

40:10.575 --> 40:12.118
You don't even like
going to the beach.

40:12.118 --> 40:13.620
This isn't about me.
Uh --

40:13.620 --> 40:15.079
No, it's not.
This is not about me.

40:15.079 --> 40:16.205
This is about you...
Okay.

40:16.205 --> 40:19.250
...staying in this
safe relationship...

40:19.250 --> 40:20.293
because you're scared.

40:20.293 --> 40:22.962
Of course I'm scared.

40:22.962 --> 40:25.048
If we do this
and it doesn't work,

40:25.048 --> 40:26.424
I'll have ruined

40:26.424 --> 40:28.092
the most important
relationship in my life.

40:28.092 --> 40:30.386
♪ Never trust a man ♪

40:30.386 --> 40:34.432
♪ I'm scared to go home ♪

40:34.432 --> 40:38.978
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have said, um --
No. Um...

40:38.978 --> 40:41.397
You're right.

40:41.397 --> 40:43.733
So we should just keep going
the way we have been, right?

40:43.733 --> 40:45.526
It's not worth the risk.

40:45.526 --> 40:47.946
♪ I'm working on safe ♪

40:47.946 --> 40:49.948
♪ I'm working on plan ♪

40:49.948 --> 40:51.199
Unless it is.

40:52.867 --> 40:58.915
♪ Life is just adjusting
to the dealer's latest hand ♪

41:01.042 --> 41:03.127
Do you want to get dinner
sometime?

41:05.380 --> 41:06.798
Yes.

41:06.798 --> 41:08.633
Yeah?
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

41:08.633 --> 41:10.635
No. Uh...

41:10.635 --> 41:12.470
I -- S-- Oh.
Okay.

41:12.470 --> 41:14.347
No, no.
It's just, um...

41:16.349 --> 41:19.602
Not yet.

41:19.602 --> 41:22.772
I owe it to Chris to end things
the right way with him.

41:24.524 --> 41:27.318
Ask me again.

41:27.318 --> 41:29.070
Later. After.

41:31.197 --> 41:32.448
Deal.

41:32.448 --> 41:34.075
♪♪

41:39.205 --> 41:42.208
-- Captions by VITAC --

41:42.208 --> 41:50.633
♪♪

41:50.633 --> 41:58.850
♪♪

41:58.850 --> 42:07.150
♪♪
